---
import Layout from '../../../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { text: 'Recruiting Team', href: '/docs/team/recruiting' },
  { text: 'Job Descriptions', href: '/docs/team/recruiting/job-descriptions-jds' },
  { text: 'UX Designer', href: '/docs/team/recruiting/job-descriptions-jds/ux-designer' }
];

---

<Layout title="Designer I">
  <main class="py-8 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <article class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto">
      <nav class="flex mb-2" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="flex items-center">
          {breadcrumbs.map((crumb, index) => (
            <li class="flex items-center">
              <a href={crumb.href} class="text-sm text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900">
                {crumb.text}
              </a>
              {index < breadcrumbs.length - 1 && (
                <span class="mx-2 text-gray-400">/</span>
              )}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ol>
      </nav>
      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <h1 class="text-[32px] font-semibold text-[#1a1f36] tracking-[-0.4px] mb-6">Designer I</h1>
        
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">About [Company Name]</h2>
        <p>Add a bit about your company here.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Role Overview</h2>
        <p>As a UX Designer at [Company Name], you will play a crucial role in crafting intuitive and engaging user experiences for our diverse range of users. This entry-level position is designed for individuals who are passionate about design, eager to learn, and ready to contribute to our dynamic team. You will work closely with senior designers and cross-functional teams to develop user-centric solutions that align with [Company Name]'s goals.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">What You'll Do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Collaborate with team members to solve specific function-level problems (e.g., adding an item to a shopping cart).</li>
          <li>Participate in user research and usability testing to gather insights and inform design decisions.</li>
          <li>Create wireframes, user flows, and prototypes to communicate design concepts effectively.</li>
          <li>Attend cross-functional meetings and contribute when asked about your particular area.</li>
          <li>Continuously improve your skills in key areas such as visual design, interaction design, and prototyping.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">What We're Looking For</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Bachelor's degree in Design, HCI, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li>
          <li>A quality portfolio showcasing your work, either from school or personal projects.</li>
          <li>Strong skills in one core area of design (e.g., visual design) and capability in two others (e.g., interaction design and prototyping).</li>
          <li>Passion for user-centered design and a desire to learn and grow in a collaborative environment.</li>
          <li>Basic understanding of design tools such as Figma, Origami, or Adobe Creative Suite.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Why Join [Company Name]</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Be part of a rapidly growing company that's shaping the future of how people connect online.</li>
          <li>Contribute to a product that impacts millions of users worldwide, driving innovation in digital experiences.</li>
          <li>Enjoy a collaborative, inclusive, and creative work environment that values diversity and fosters professional growth.</li>
          <li>Benefit from a competitive compensation package, flexible work arrangements, and a commitment to work-life balance.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mt-8">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">[Company Name] is committed to providing a competitive compensation package. Our cash compensation amount for this role is targeted at $X-$X in X area. Final offer amounts are determined by multiple factors, including candidate expertise, the scope of role and level, and may vary from the amounts listed above.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
